
[1]lucre

   LU'CRE, n. lu'ker. [L. lucrum.] Gain in money or goods; profit; usually
   in an ill sense, or with the sense of something base or unworthy.

   The lust of lucre, and the dread of death.

   A bishop must be blameless - not given to filthy lucre. Titus 1.
